main event: A civilian reported seeing a bright blue-white light maneuvering in the sky in Wayne, New Jersey on January 11, 1966.
interesting points: The sighting lasted approximately 22 seconds to 3-4 minutes., The object was reported to have an erratic flight path., The observer compared the brightness of the light to that of an aircraft strobe light., The conclusion of the report suggested it was likely aircraft., No physical evidence or photographs were available.
sighted object: bright blue-white light in the sky
witness description: The witness described the object as a bright light with colors seen on its surface.
